title: Pearl Jam - Indio CA.(Live 2-CD) 1993 ak320
description:
Pearl Jam - Indio CA.(Live 2-CD) 1993 ak320

Recorded at Empire Polo Fields in Indio, CA 11/5/93. The infamous shoe/throwing show. The show from which the X-Mas single "Ramblings (live)" was taken from as well as "Blood" from the Daughter CD single.
I see they are still putting out material that's nice. But Ill stick to the older content which I enjoy much more. Like this classic show from my home state (Now on Fire).

On the evening of November 5, 1993, Pearl Jam performed before almost 25,000 fans that stood and sat through the night on the lawns of Indio, California previously rock-festival free Empire Polo Club. (This show is well-known among fans because halfway through the set, fans in the pit began pelting the band with shoes, provoking Vedder and the band to walk off stage, only to come out and play the rest of the set from behind a wall of speakers.) Although band management had chosen this untested and under-developed site as part of a boycott of Ticketmaster and the Southern California auditoriums it controlled, the event established the new venue's suitability for large-scale rock events
